      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Good race of several winning hopes. KALIMNA VIEWS (5) is a former Victorian making debut in this area. Best figures stack up and has won fresh. Yet to start on dirt but ran very well only try on the Pakenham synthetic in a rating most of these would only dream on. Should hit the ground running for the new barn if she jumps cleanly. In Victoria had a habit of getting back. VIACONI (7) doesn't win out of turn but was a dominant winner last time and with the claim here looks nicely placed again. Can go on with it. MISS BLACK DIAMOND (6) was a winner fresh then below best last time. Fitter and gets a chance to atone. TIGERS ROAR (3) is flying, winning both runs this time in. Has the speed to overcome the tricky draw and will give a sight again. RUNAWAY TYCOON (2) is fitter and can sneak into the finish.",
